    <statement><p>Simplify the following expression, and if applicable, write the restricted domain on the simplified expression.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{{\frac{3y-y^{2}}{y^{2}+2y-15}}=}</m> <fillin characters="19" name="AnSwEr0001"/></p>
</statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>-\frac{y}{y+5}, y\ne 3</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
    <solution><p>To simplify the expression, we first factor both the numerator and denominator, and then cross out common factors:</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{\begin{aligned}
   {\frac{3y-y^{2}}{y^{2}+2y-15}} \amp = \frac{{y\mathopen{}\left(3-y\right)}}{{\left(y-3\right)\mathopen{}\left(y+5\right)}} \\
                     \amp = \frac{{-y\mathopen{}\left(y-3\right)}}{{\left(y-3\right)\mathopen{}\left(y+5\right)}} \\
                     \amp = {-\frac{y}{y+5}, y\ne 3}
\end{aligned}
    }</m></p>
<p>Since the factor <m>y-3</m> was crossed out, the domain condition lost during the simplification is <m>y \ne 3</m>.</p>
<p>Note that we used the formula <m>3-y = -(y-3)</m>.</p>
</solution>
